#To download/Example: SRR31641737 (Run name)

#Option 1 
prefetch SRR31641737 #Download the complete file SRR23875742.sra, but do not extract it. Good for when you're not analyzing it right now. It takes up less space.
fasterq-dump SRR31641737.sra #To extract the fastq files

#Option 2 
fasterq-dump SRR31641737 #Download and extract the fastq file all at once.

Downloading multiple files at once: create a list with the SSRs, one below the other, in a text file.
#1) Create a list of the SSRs, one below the other, in a text file.

#2) Run the command
for SRR in $(cat list_SRR.txt); do prefetch "$SRR" && fasterq-dump "$SRR"; done

# or, if you just want to download: 
for SRR in $(cat list_SRR.txt); do prefetch "$SRR"; done
